# Adding a social provider

Ship **backend + web + docs + public channel landing page + feature bento showcases** in one change. Reference implementations: **Threads** (single-step OAuth), **Instagram (Business)** (Page picker + compose settings), **Facebook Page** (Meta OAuth + link-preview settings). Public landing + bento references: **facebook**, **threads** in `publicChannelConfig.ts` and `web/src/lib/ui/templates/bento/minor-templates/`. Full guide: `web/src/content/docs/social-integration/add-provider.md`.

## Identifier contract

Use one kebab-case slug everywhere: `provider.identifier`, DB `provider_identifier`, OAuth callback `/integration/oauth/{identifier}`, `getLaunchProviderConfig`, CLI filters, docs filenames, **`publicChannelConfig` `slug` / `platformId`**, and `/channels/{slug}`. Do not fork slugs between layers.

## Backend (required)

1. **`SocialProvider` class** ŌĆö `backend/integrations/providers/{id}/` implementing `social.integrations.interface.ts`: OAuth (`generateAuthUrl`, `authenticate`), `post`, `maxLength`, scopes. Split publish logic into helpers (e.g. `*GraphPublish.ts`) when non-trivial.
2. **Register** ŌĆö add `new YourProvider()` in `backend/integrations/integrationManager.ts` (no new REST routes).
3. **Config** ŌĆö secrets only via `config.integrations.*` in `GlobalConfig.ts` + `.env.development.example`. Redirect URI: `oauthFrontendOrigin()` + `oauthFrontendSocialCallbackPath(identifier)`.
4. **Between-steps OAuth** ŌĆö when `isBetweenSteps: true`: implement `pages()` + `fetchPageInformation()`; extend `IntegrationConnectionService.saveProviderPageForOrganization` / `preservesUserTokenForRefresh` if user token must stay in `refresh_token` (Meta Page pattern).
5. **Provider settings at publish** ŌĆö read from `postDetails.settings.providerSettings`. Accept **flat CLI keys** and **nested web buckets** (e.g. `providerSettings.url` and `providerSettings.facebook.url`). Export a resolver + unit tests beside publish helpers.
6. **Tests** ŌĆö unit tests for OAuth edge cases, publish payload shaping, and connection save when behavior differs.

## Web (composer + connect)

Connect catalog is backend-driven; composer wiring is **opt-in per provider**.

1. **Launch config** ŌĆö `web/src/lib/ui/components/posts/providers/{id}/{id}.provider.ts` (`LaunchProviderConfig`: limits, `postComment`, optional `checkValidity` / `checkValidityAsync`). Register in `providers/index.ts` ŌåÆ `getLaunchProviderConfig`.
2. **Preview** ŌĆö `{id}Preview.svelte` + branch in `ShowAllProviders.svelte`.
3. **OAuth Page picker** (when `isBetweenSteps`) ŌĆö config in `web/src/lib/integrations/continue-provider/{id}.ts`, register in `continue-provider/index.ts`; reuse `IntegrationContinue.svelte` + `ContinueIntegration.presenter.svelte.ts` + `ContinueProviderPicker.svelte`.
4. **Compose settings** (optional) ŌĆö `{id}Settings.svelte`; wire provider branch in `SettingsAccordion.svelte`; emit **only that providerŌĆÖs bucket** (do not write unrelated `threads` / `instagram` defaults). Add types/helpers in `provider.types.ts` and `{id}.provider.ts`.
5. **Labels** ŌĆö `web/src/data/social-providers.ts` when the slug is new.

Keep composer validation aligned with backend publish rules (`checkValidity` Ōåö `validateCreatePost` / publish helper constraints).

## Public channel landing page (SEO marketing)

Routes and UI are **generic** ŌĆö adding a channel is a **catalog entry only** (no new `+page` files per slug).

| Artifact | Path / URL |
| --- | --- |
| Content catalog | `web/src/lib/content/constants/publicChannelConfig.ts` |
| Route helpers | `web/src/lib/area-public/constants/getRootPathPublicChannels.ts` (`channels`, `channels/{slug}`) |
| Hub route | `/channels` ŌĆö `web/src/routes/(public)/channels/+page.server.ts` lists `listPublicChannelsForHub()` |
| Detail route | `/channels/{slug}` ŌĆö `web/src/routes/(public)/channels/[slug]/+page.server.ts` resolves `getAvailablePublicChannelBySlug(slug)` (404 when missing or `available: false`) |
| Page template | `web/src/lib/ui/templates/PublicChannelLandingPage.svelte` |
| Hub grid | `web/src/lib/ui/templates/landing-page/PublicChannelsHubGrid.svelte` |
| Hero | `web/src/lib/ui/templates/landing-page/PublicChannelHero.svelte` |

Navbar/footer link to `/channels` is already in `web/src/lib/config/constants/config.ts`; **do not add per-channel nav entries**.

### Catalog entry (`PublicChannelLandingPage`)

Add a constant in `publicChannelConfig.ts` and append it to `PUBLIC_CHANNEL_LANDING_PAGES` (before or instead of a coming-soon stub).

| Field | Rule |
| --- | --- |
| `slug`, `platformId` | Same kebab-case slug as `provider.identifier` |
| `platformLabel` | Human-readable name (e.g. `Facebook`, `X`) |
| `icon` | `icons.{Provider}.name` from `$data/icons` |
| `heroTitle`, `heroDescription` | Platform-specific H1 and lead copy |
| `metaTitle`, `metaDescription`, `keywords` | SEO; title becomes `{metaTitle} \| {companyName}` on the page |
| `featureSections` | **3 sections** typical: subtitle, title, description, `bentoId` (preferred), `mediaOnRight` (alternate left/right). See **Feature bento showcases** below ŌĆö do **not** ship go-live pages with generic `/landing/*.mp4` placeholders when the provider has a bento set. |
| `faqSubtitle`, `faqTitle`, `faqDescription`, `faqItems` | Channel-specific FAQ; JSON-LD `FAQPage` is generated in `+page.server.ts` |
| `docsPath` | Setup guide path, e.g. `/docs/social-integration/{id}` ŌĆö must match the doc you ship |
| `available` | `true` when the detail page should be live; `false` for hub-only ŌĆ£Coming soonŌĆØ |

**Coming soon (provider not ready):** add a minimal stub in `COMING_SOON_CHANNELS` with `available: false`, empty hero/FAQ/feature arrays, and a short `metaDescription`. Hub shows a badge; `/channels/{slug}` returns 404.

**Go live:** replace the stub with a full entry (or flip `available: true` and fill content). Ship **provider-specific bento showcases** for all three feature sections (see below). Copy must describe **only features already implemented** ŌĆö do not oversell.

### Landing copy voice (problem-first)

Write `heroTitle`, `heroDescription`, `featureSections`, `audienceCards`, and FAQ answers for **the person scheduling posts** ŌĆö lead with the pain or outcome, not a settings checklist.

| Prefer | Avoid |
| --- | --- |
| What the user struggles with or wants (reach, consistency, time saved, approval control) | Feature inventories (`privacy_level`, `providerSettings`, toggle names, API paths) |
| Plain outcomes (ŌĆ£queue to your inbox, pick trending audio in the appŌĆØ) |
| Second person (ŌĆ£youŌĆØ, ŌĆ£your postsŌĆØ, ŌĆ£your workspaceŌĆØ) | Passive product specs (ŌĆ£supports X, Y, Z settingsŌĆØ) |

**`featureSections` pattern:**

- **`subtitle`** ŌĆö user problem or job-to-be-done (e.g. `Trending audio`, `Bulk scheduling`), not an internal label (`Compose settings`).
- **`title`** ŌĆö outcome in **three comma-separated phrases**; `HeroWithLeftMedia` / `HeroWithRightMedia` split on `,` into separate lines. Each phrase must read cleanly on its own line ŌĆö do not break mid-thought (e.g. `ŌĆ”TikTok, add the soundŌĆ”` renders as `,add` on the next line).
- **`description`** ŌĆö problem ŌåÆ how OpenQuok helps ŌåÆ result; mention shipped workflow steps the bento shows.

**Reference:** TikTok `featureSections[1]` in `publicChannelConfig.ts` ŌĆö inbox drafts + manual trending audio for algorithm reach; bento still shows composer settings, but copy sells the user problem.

**Audience cards** ŌĆö who they are + what pain is solved (e.g. founders shipping product while TikTok runs), not role labels with feature lists.

Agent skill files and setup docs stay **feature-accurate and terse** ŌĆö do not paste landing marketing prose into `resources/{id}-examples.md` (see below).

### Feature bento showcases (required at go-live)

Each live `/channels/{slug}` page renders three feature rows via `HeroWithLeftMedia` / `HeroWithRightMedia`. When `featureSections[].bentoId` is set, the route renders `BentoPublicChannelFeature` instead of a static video (`web/src/routes/(public)/channels/[slug]/+page.svelte`).

**When adding or go-live-ing a provider, implement bento for all three feature sections** ŌĆö same bar as composer preview and analytics wiring. Reference **facebook** and **threads**.

| Layer | Path / action |
| --- | --- |
| Bento ID union | Add `{slug}-ŌĆ”` literals to `web/src/lib/content/constants/publicChannelFeatureBentoConfig.ts` |
| Router component | Branch in `web/src/lib/ui/templates/bento/minor-templates/BentoPublicChannelFeature.svelte` |
| Catalog wiring | Set `bentoId` (not `imageSrc`) on each of the three `featureSections` in `publicChannelConfig.ts` |
| Mock data | `web/src/lib/ui/templates/bento/minor-templates/{slug}/{slug}LandingMock.ts` (+ optional `{slug}LandingKanbanMock.ts`, `{slug}LandingAnalyticsMock.ts`) |
| Preview panels | Reuse **real** product UI read-only: kanban (`KanbanBoardFilters` + `KanbanColumn`), composer (`PicksSocialsComponent`, `ShowAllProviders`, `SettingsAccordion` with `embedded`, provider settings), analytics (`RenderAnalyticsGrid` + metric seeds matching backend `analytics()`) |
| Wrappers | `Bento{Provider}{Feature}.svelte` ŌåÆ `BentoCard` + `BentoGridOneCol` (mirror `BentoFacebookBulkScheduling.svelte`, `BentoThreadsMediaReplies.svelte`) |

**Typical three-section themes** (pick what the provider actually ships):

1. **Bulk scheduling** ŌĆö kanban / calendar batching (`*-bulk-scheduling`).
2. **Compose differentiator** ŌĆö provider-specific composer or settings (`*-video-links`, `*-media-replies`, `{id}Settings` in `SettingsAccordion`, etc.).
3. **Insights** ŌĆö platform analytics dashboard (`*-insights`) when `SocialProvider.analytics()` is implemented; otherwise choose another shipped capability and still use a bento (do not fall back to generic MP4s at go-live).

**Mock preview conventions:**

- Outer wrapper: `pointer-events-none select-none`; pass `disabled={true}` / `noop` handlers so panels are visual-only.
- Prefer `SettingsAccordion` with `embedded` and `open={true}` for settings previews (see `BentoFacebookSettingsPreview.svelte`, `BentoThreadsComposerPreview.svelte`).
- Keep landing mocks **short**: `ThreadRepliesEditor` ŌåÆ `hideProviderHelp={true}`; nested editors ŌåÆ `compactEditor` / `SettingsAccordion` ŌåÆ `compactEditors`; limit mock reply rows to one when showing follow-ups.
- Mock channel view models live beside previews (`CreateSocialPostChannelViewModel` with `identifier` matching the provider slug).
- Feature copy (title, description, FAQ) must match what the bento demonstrates.

**Do not** use competitor landing pages as a feature checklist; document only OpenQuok behavior.

### CTA (detail pages)

Use **one CTA label everywhere**, matching `web/src/lib/ui/templates/LandingPage.svelte`:

- **Text:** `Get Started For Free`
- **Href:** `/pricing`

Wire through `PublicChannelLandingPage.svelte` (`secondaryCtaText` / `secondaryCtaHref`) into the hero and every feature section. **Do not** add login-dependent CTAs (`Start for $0`, `Open workspace`), a secondary ŌĆ£Setup guideŌĆØ button, or a bottom CTA block.

### Load / page conventions

- `+page.server.ts` files own SSR, meta tags (`createMetaData`), and JSON-LD schema.
- `+page.ts` follows the universal load pattern (`await parent()`, merge `isLoggedIn` / roles on the client branch). See **web-sveltekit-universal-page-load**.
- `+page.svelte` exposes load fields via `$derived(data.*)` ŌĆö do not pass `isLoggedIn` into `PublicChannelLandingPage`.

